Financial Institutions Act
Insurance Society Exemption Regulation
Interpretation
1  In this regulation "Act" means the Financial Institutions Act.

Exemption from section 196
2  Section 196 of the Act does not apply to a society, described in that section, in respect of a contract between it and a member of the society if each of the following conditions is fulfilled:

(a)the society's assets exceed its liabilities by at least $3 million;

(b)the contract with the member

(i)provides health care benefits or income replacement benefits covering a period of disability because of illness or injury, and

(ii)pays insurance money not exceeding $100 000 during a 24 month benefit period.

[Provisions of the Financial Institutions Act, R.S.B.C. 1996, c. 141, relevant to the enactment of this regulation: section 289 (4) (o)]
